Why all this weight on 
my shoulders? I didn't 
ask to be the inspector 
of the world. Now, I don’t 
know how to end this 
poem. On “Torment” I 
wrote: “You may want 
to find a way to 
suggest ironic 
distance between the poet 
and speaker.” I couldn’t 
figure out what else, 
to responsible 
children, there was to 
say. “I fucked up 
bad”: Justin cracks his 
neck, didn’t he have a house 
key around his neck, 
didn’t he have a pager, 
an electrical 
